Okay, this is the map that some of you have been waiting for. xc_waterleak_final is finally here (:D).

The basic concept of the an xc map is to climb to the top. In this map, its more escaping than xcing, and that to escape in the quickest, cleanest way possible (Out of the 2 glass doors in the reception which is the end of the map). The map is set in a surfing trainging facility, but you are not here for surfing. Recently a waterleak broke out, and you are called over to fix it. Before you can do any maintinance, the power goes out, all main units and doors have gone offline (im sorry rad wasnt run in the map, if it would the lights would of gone offline in result of this waterleak for more effect, seems my map has something against vrad and crashes during compilation). 

Note: When u get to the spiked wall, go to the botton left spike and hit e, not too close or your dead. Also during the boss fight on the roof of the congratz room, since many complained about lack on ammo during the bb_map i submitted, i dropepd loads of guns on the roof for you to kill it, well more than enough ammo.

If have any questions about the map, or experience any graphic and gameplay bugs, talk to me on xfire:carlthecat is my username.

sv_airaccelerate 100 and mp_limitteams 0 is required for play. ALSO DONT USE INFINITE HEALTH. Ive explained why on the right.

A tropical jump map I made for CS:S.

Very pretty in the use of the sky and water.
It has a warm tropical feel and just damn fun to play.

3 Islands, each island has a unique jump course connected by a mini-jump course to get to the next island.

At the end, you can choose to restart by stepping into the teleporter or go into the water.
Why go into the water?
Because an extra course will rise up from the water, for people to jump on if they finish before others.
When you finish that and you are done bragging about it to your friends about how awesome your are, you can restart from there too.

Enjoy it. This took me a wile.

PLEASE ASSESS! I WANT TO KNOW HOW IM DOING! ^^

-Disturbed

I made an extra mission for those who like to explore a little. (The real climb ends at the apartment with the dude watching the telly), but if you collect 7 keys found in the map you'll access a nice bonus with a few surprises! (Collect keys with your Use button)

---SPOILER, KEY LOCATIONS---

1. On the bed in the first apartment.
2. Once you climbed out of the blue maintance room, open the middle door and search your right for a hook on the floor. Open it.
3. Once you climbed over the wall, it's between the dumpster and the green car. It's pretty hard to see if you don't have the flashlight.
4. Go to the courtyard and find it between a few oil drums on the platform.
5. In the next apartment, shoot the box on the table.
6. Next apartment, next to the couch.
7. Lying on the floor in the last room.

---END OF SPOILER---

Please assess!!!

This is a short climb map set in some Greek-inspired ruins.  The first play through of the map requires some exploration and the path may not be immediately obvious.  Some areas have multiple paths and shortcuts that require skill.  This map was made to be played without checkpoints and with the timer, though you can play it however you like.  There is a 3D skybox if you set "r_3dsky 1".  Soundscapes are used within the map as well as some looped ambient sounds (though the ambient_generics don't seem to play on non-LAN servers).

At the end, there is a tone matrix that can be set between pure notes or drum and bass.  Shoot the tiles within the border to activate tones and make some simple tunes.

Materials used can be found in credits.txt of the download archive.

A mario jump map I made. 

Has multiple jump courses to jump on, the ? Boxes at the beginning of the map can spawn weapons when jumped under.

Music is played throughout the map, from the theme of super Mario.
Custom sounds are included to add to the experience.


The reason why the map is in fullbright, is because lighting looked really ugly and looked more of a mario theme if it was in fullbright.

As a mapper who is against the idea of floating jump platforms, I used some only because Mario games actually have stuff floating in mid air.


Enjoy this map

-Disturbed
